                <note rend="inline" type="source">724.3415/1248: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Morgan</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rio de Janeiro</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-06-29T16:00:00-03:00"
                            >June 29—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received June 29—3:15 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>42. Brazilian Minister for Foreign Affairs continues to be seriously concerned
                    with the Bolivian-Paraguayan situation. Commander of <pb facs="0852" n="738"
                        xml:id="pg_738"/> Brazilian flotilla on Parana River has eported that the
                    river frontier between Bolivia and Paraguay has been closed. Minister will be
                    glad to deliver any warning or statement which with the support of the American
                    Government he may communicate to Bolivian and Paraguayan Ministers stationed at
                    Rio de Janeiro.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Morgan</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
